This species occurs in Central Asian mountains north of Altai. Distribution in China – Xinjiang (Aerjin mountain, Yaziquan) (
Chen 1996
).

This recently described species known only from Xinjiang (
Luo, Vinokurov 2011
).

The species was described from southern Xinjiang (oases Nia and Kerya). Type specimens are probably lost (
Cobben 1985
). Three specimens ( 1 ɗ 2 Ψ) collected in the Tisnaf River at the altitude of 1500–2000 m a.s.l. are kept in the Zoological Institute RAS (S.-Petersburg).

Palearctic. The species was recorded from Xinjiang by Chen & Lindskog (
1994
).

Trans-Euroasian. The species was recorded from Xinjiang by Chen & Lindskog (
1994
).

Distributed in Europe and Western Siberia, isolated in Central Asian mountains from Turkmenistan (Ashkhabad) to Southeastern Kazakhstan , Eastern Kyrghyzstan, Western Mongolia and Kashmir (
Vinokurov, 2004
). In China is known from Sichuan (Chen, Lindskog, 1994 ). So far has not been recorded from Xinjiang.

Multiregional. The species was recorded from Xinjiang by Chen & Lindskog (
1994
).

Trans-Palearctic. The species was recorded from Xinjiang (Arjin, Yaziquan; Aketao, Aketashsi, Wyutake; Heitan County, Kashitashi) (
Chen 1996
).

Holarctic. The species was recorded from Xinjiang by Chen & Lindskog (
1994
).

Distributed in Eastern Kazakhstan , Southern Siberia, and Western Mongolia (
Vinokurov, 2004
). So far has not been known from China . The nearest localities of the species are in the northern slope of Jungarian Alatau Range, where this species inhabit forests near riversides and forestry canyons (
Cobben, 1985
).

South Palearctic. The species was recorded from Xinjiang by Chen & Lindskog (
1994
).
